datasource: Tosco, Mauro. 2001. The Dhaasanac language: grammar, texts, vocabulary of a Cushitic language of Ethiopia. Kuschitische Sprachstudien. vol. 17. Köln: Köppe Verlag. [MT01]

Vowels.inventory: i e a o u; ii ee aa oo uu; ie [front falling diphthong] uo [back falling diphthong]

Prosody.Type: 'Dh ia a tonal accent language in which accent is realised as a rise in pitch (high tone).' [MT01p34]

geodemoTXT: The Western Omo-Tana language, Dhaasanac is spoken in Ethiopia and Kenya in villages along the lower Omo river and near Lake Turkana.

fuor.gloss: take the animals out of pen

ghee.gloss: (suppletive for yaal 'stand' in Imprtv and Perf Pl)
